B) margin-bottom: [status bar height]; is the correct solution. It adds space below the content equal to the height of the status bar, ensuring the last line is visible when scrolling.
C) position: relative; alone wouldn't solve the issue of the obscured last line.
D) z-index: 1; might place the content above the status bar visually, but it wouldn't create the necessary space to see the last line.

The key is to create additional space at the bottom of the scrollable area equal to the height of the status bar. This pushes the content up, allowing users to scroll fully to the last line without it being hidden behind the status bar.

